This paper is primarily focused on image semantic segmentation, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) category. The proposed method involves using a scene recommender to suggest adding specific scene contexts to the target dataset, which could be seen as a machine learning (cs.LG) approach. Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges of weakly supervised learning, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of natural language processing techniques to analyze scene context could also be seen as relevant to computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the paper involves experiments with image data, which could be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM).
